<h3>threat</h3>

A risk is unsaved people not being reached for salvation. People often help explain the gospel, but if not careful, the app could add to risk too. The table identifies some possible risks from the app.

<table border=1>
<caption>risk/threat</caption>
<tr>
<td>Complexity: people not wanting to invest long times to understand the app before helping maintain it. Possible result is no maintenance and the app being lost.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Changing programming languages. Caesar was trying to avoid C/C++. Any changes may be a lot of effort to get back to a functional state.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Marketing systems (Google play, Apple store) being unable to capture the interest of potential operators/readers.</td>
</tr>

</table>
